# Best Practices & Code Quality

## Code Organization
- Keep files focused and single-purpose
- Extract complex logic into separate functions or hooks
- Group related code together
- Use meaningful file and directory names
- Follow FSD layer structure strictly

## Naming Conventions
- Use descriptive, self-documenting names
- Avoid abbreviations unless widely understood
- Use consistent naming patterns across the codebase
- Follow established conventions for each layer

## Comments & Documentation
- Write self-documenting code, minimize comments
- Add comments only when code intent is not obvious
- Document complex algorithms or business logic
- Use JSDoc for public APIs when helpful
- Keep comments up-to-date with code changes

## Error Handling
- Always handle errors gracefully
- Provide user-friendly error messages
- Log errors appropriately for debugging
- Use proper error boundaries
- Validate data at boundaries (API, forms)

## Performance
- Optimize images with `next/image`
- Use code splitting and lazy loading
- Minimize bundle size
- Use React Query caching effectively
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders

## Security
- Never expose sensitive data in client code
- Validate and sanitize user input
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Follow security best practices for authentication
- Protect API routes appropriately

## Testing Considerations
- Write testable code (pure functions, clear dependencies)
- Keep components and logic separated
- Use dependency injection patterns
- Make functions pure when possible

## Git & Version Control
- See detailed Git rules in `git.mdc`
- Always follow Conventional Commits format
- Run tests and linter before committing

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Provide proper ARIA labels
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Maintain sufficient color contrast
- Test with screen readers

## Code Review
- Review your own code before submitting
- Check for common mistakes and patterns
- Ensure consistency with codebase
- Verify FSD import rules are followed
